The continuous homomorphism $\Delta:G \rightarrow \mathbb{R}^{\times}_+$ is defined by
\begin{equation*}
\int_G f(xy)dx = \Delta(y)\int_Gf(x)dx
\end{equation*}
where $dx$ is a left Haar measure on $G$. $G$ is called unimodular if and only if $\Delta(y) = 1$. Are nilpotent Lie groups unimodular?

